  array('id' => '2467','book_id' => 'B03759','title' => 'British Salmonidae','author' => 'Jardine,Sir William','publication_year' => '1979','publisher' => 'Decimus','edition' => 'Ltd Edn Rep (321/500)','pages' => NULL,'size' => '10','book_condition' => 'Mint','jacket_condition' => 'NDJAP - slipcase VF+','cost_price' => '75','valuation' => '500','add_date' => '02/2018','sold_date' => NULL,'sold_price' => NULL,'buyer_name' => NULL,'buyer_email' => NULL,'comment' => 'Decimus, London, 1979, #297 of 500 copies, facsimile reprint of the original edition in 12 separate parts, published between 1839 and 1841. Illustrated with 12 well printed color plates, and color and b&w text figures. 18.5" x 25". Green cloth, brown leather spine, spine scuffed, large leather front cover label, marbled endpapers. One page of text per plate, plus a loose 4 page pamphlet by Alwyne Wheeler on the history of this work and its author. "The plates of British Salmonidae are unique.the central subject being coloured and portrayed against an etched background.the background forms an integral part of the plate.Jardine by his own studies was able to eradicate much of the confusion which had caused earlier naturalists to accept so many species of salmonoid fishes.the colourful 10 of twelve plates.is a fitting testimony to Jardine\'s skill with pencil and brush and to the technical ability of his engraver, William Lizars". An impressive work, with splendid plates. By far the largest book that we have ever sold, measuring 25" x 37" when open. Internally, the condition is very fine. The binding is very good in a scuffed but good cloth covered slipcase, with a large leather cover label.','status' => NULL),
