  array('id' => '2781','book_id' => 'B03845','title' => 'The Western Angler','author' => 'Hig-Brown,Roderick L','publication_year' => '1939','publisher' => 'The Derrydale Press','edition' => '1st Ltd (929/950)','pages' => '392','size' => '8','book_condition' => 'Cvrs sl dirty o/w F','jacket_condition' => 'NDJAP','cost_price' => '200','valuation' => '500','add_date' => '09/2018','sold_date' => NULL,'sold_price' => NULL,'buyer_name' => NULL,'buyer_email' => NULL,'comment' => 'The Derrydale Press, New York, 1939. First edition, no. 929 of 950 copies. First edition, no. 929 of 950 copies. Illustrated with plates in color and in black and white, not one of the versions with THE FOLDING MAP IN VOLUME ONE. 2 vols. 8. A beautiful and monumental work. Notes Frazier, "Approximately one third of the 950 sets of this book were issued with the fold-out map opposite page 3 of Volume 1. The other two-thirds of this set were issued without the fold-out map." Siegel does not explain the reason for this omission, only that it exists. A SCARCE AND HIGHLY DESIRABLE ANGLING DERRYDALE. Siegel 156; Frazier H-1-a, H-1-b; Cave A21 Original red cloth. Very good plus set in superior condition (minor exterior soiling), internally fresh Illustrated with plates in color and in black and white. Very rare book also. With bookplate of Col. Henry Siegel & also lavishly inscribed to "Mac in Santiago, Chile") with a Xmas card with photos of authors kids included with best wishes from author and wife','status' => NULL),
